Step 2: Create a systemd service

Make a service file so systemd manages it:

sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/main.service


Paste this inside:

[Unit]
Description=Run main.py on boot
After=network.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/home/pi/start_main.sh
WorkingDirectory=/home/pi
StandardOutput=inherit
StandardError=inherit
Restart=always
User=pi

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target


Save & exit.

Step 3: Enable and start the service
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable main.service
sudo systemctl start main.service

Step 4: Check if it works
systemctl status main.service


If you reboot:

sudo reboot


Your main.py will auto-run at startup 🚀